                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18370814-1750-offence-1 t18370814-name-146"></join>Francis Nalder</persName>, and others.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18370814-name-147" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18370814-name-147" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370814-name-147" type="surname" value="LINGHAM"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370814-name-147" type="given" value="RANDALL"></interp>RANDALL LINGHAM</persName>
                  </hi>. I am in the employ of Francis Nalder, and others, warehousemen in Cheapside. We lost some ribbon, and we were ordered to watch—on the 10th of August the prisoner came down with a piece of gauze in his hand—he looked round, saw no one there, and took half a piece of ribbon, put it into his hat, and went up stairs—I followed him, and he went up to the second floor—I met him at the bottom of the stairs, and charged him with it—he denied it—I gave him in charge of Mr. Nalder—this is the ribbon he took—it was not found on him in my presence.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner. Q.</hi> Have you not frequently known me bring you back goods when I have had more than was written down in the ticket? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes you have—you were in the habit of working for Mr. Glover.</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183708140021"></xptr>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18370814-name-148" type="witnessName">
